#, no-wrap
msgid "Neovim is described in detail on its [dedicated page](install_nvim.md) so we will just dwell on the main features, which are:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/index.md:94
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/install_nvim.md:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "Performance: Very fast.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/index.md:96
#, no-wrap
msgid "Customizable: Wide ecosystem of plugins and themes.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/index.md:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "Syntax highlighting: Integration with Treesitter and LSP, (requires some additional configurations).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/index.md:100
#, no-wrap
msgid "Multiplatform: Linux, Windows and macOS\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/index.md:102
#, no-wrap
msgid "License: Mit: A short and simple permissive license with conditions requiring only the preservation of copyright and license notices.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/index.md:103
#, no-wrap
msgid "LSP"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/index.md:106
#, no-wrap
msgid "What is the **L**anguage **S**erver **P**rotocol?\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/index.md:108
#, no-wrap
msgid "A language server is a standardized language library that uses its own procedure (protocol) to provide support for functions such as autocomplete, goto definition, or mouseover definitions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/index.md:110
#, no-wrap
msgid "The idea behind the Language Server Protocol (LSP) is to standardize the communication protocol between tools and servers, so that a single language server can be reused in multiple development tools. In this way, developers can simply integrate these libraries into their editors and reference existing language infrastructures, instead of customizing their code to include them.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/index.md:111
#, no-wrap
msgid "tree-sitter"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/index.md:114
#, no-wrap
msgid "[Tree-sitter](https://tree-sitter.github.io/tree-sitter/) basically consists of two components: a parser generator, and an incremental parsing library. It can build a syntactic tree of the source file and efficiently update it with each change.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
